Think of Docker Compose as a "Master Remote Control" for your entire project. It allows you to run multiple containers (like Backend + Database) with just one command.

Installation & Setup
sudo apt-get install docker-compose-v2: Use this command to install the Docker Compose tool on your system.

The YAML File: You write a docker-compose.yml file to list all your services, ports, and volumes in one place.

Essential Commands
docker-compose up -d: Reads your file and starts all containers in the background. No need to remember long commands!

docker-compose down: Stops and removes all containers, networks, and images related to the project.

docker-compose ps: Shows the live status of all containers managed by the Compose file.

docker-compose logs -f: Shows live logs for all your containers at once so you can see what’s happening.
